        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 8:21AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 821 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Salem in Saline County, or near Benton, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Park Hill...                      Otter Creek...
Natural Steps...                  Palarm...
Mayflower...                      Gravel Ridge...
Hillcrest Neighborhood...         Austin in Lonoke County...
Vilonia...                        Olmstead...
Roland in Pulaski County...       Bryant...
Macon...                          El Paso...
The Heights...                    North Little Rock Airport...
Congo...                          Lakewood...
Camp Robinson...                  Mabelvale...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
